com.arkoisystems.arkoicompiler.stage.syntaxAnalyzer.parser

Class AbstractParser<T extends AbstractSyntaxAST>

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.arkoisystems.arkoicompiler.stage.syntaxAnalyzer.parser.AbstractParser<T>
  • Type Parameters:
    T - the AbstractSyntaxAST which should define this class.
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    AnnotationParser, ArgumentDefinitionParser, BlockParser, ExpressionParser, FunctionParser, OperableParser, StatementParser, TypeParser

    public abstract class AbstractParser<T extends AbstractSyntaxAST>
extends java.lang.Object
    This class is used to define a AbstractParser for a specific AbstractSyntaxAST. So you can easily create an AST without any problems. Also this class is capable to test the current AbstractToken if it could be parsed by this AST.

    • Method Detail

      • parse

        public abstract T parse(AbstractSyntaxAST parentAST,
                        SyntaxAnalyzer syntaxAnalyzer)
        This method is used to parse the specified AST. Also it will pass some arguments to it like the parentAST (AbstractSyntaxAST) or the SyntaxAnalyzer. If this method returns null it indicates that an error occurred.
        Parameters:
        parentAST - the AbstractSyntaxAST in which this AST is getting parsed.
        syntaxAnalyzer - the SyntaxAnalyzer which is used to call methods like SyntaxAnalyzer.matchesCurrentToken(TokenType) etc.
        Returns:
        null if an error occurred or the specified AbstractSyntaxAST.

      • canParse

        public abstract boolean canParse(AbstractSyntaxAST parentAST,
                                 SyntaxAnalyzer syntaxAnalyzer)
        This method is used to check if the current AbstractToken is capable to parse the specified AST. If not it will return false or true if it would work.
        Parameters:
        parentAST - the AbstractSyntaxAST in which this AST is getting parsed.
        syntaxAnalyzer - the SyntaxAnalyzer which is used to call methods like SyntaxAnalyzer.matchesCurrentToken(TokenType) etc.
        Returns:
        false if it's not capable to parse the current AbstractToken or true if it does.
